  schema:name "Pyotr Kropotkin" ;
  schema:description "Pyotr Kropotkin (1842–1921) was a Russian geographer, naturalist, and anarchist theorist who grounded the case for non-hierarchical society in biological and historical evidence of cooperation as a factor of evolution." ;
